    <!-- About Section -->
    <section class="section" id="about">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">What is Signal Processing?</h2>
            <div class="content-wrapper">
                <div class="text-content">
                    <p>Signal Processing is a specialized branch of electrical engineering that focuses on analyzing, modifying, and extracting information from signals. A signal is any time-varying or spatial-varying quantity that carries information, such as audio, video, images, sensor readings, or communication transmissions. Signal processing techniques enable us to enhance, filter, compress, and interpret these signals for various applications.</p>
                    <p>As a signal processing engineer, you'll work on developing algorithms and systems that manipulate signals to achieve desired outcomes. This might involve removing noise from audio recordings, compressing images for efficient storage, extracting features from biomedical signals for diagnosis, or designing filters for communication systems.</p>
                    <p>This field combines elements of mathematics, computer science, and electrical engineering to create powerful tools for understanding and working with the vast amounts of data generated in our digital world. Signal processing is fundamental to technologies we use every day, from smartphones and digital cameras to medical imaging devices and autonomous vehicles.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Areas Section -->
    <section class="section bg-dark" id="key-areas">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">Key Areas of Study</h2>
            <p class="section-intro">Signal Processing encompasses several specialized areas that form the foundation of modern signal analysis and manipulation:</p>
            
            <div class="cards-grid three-columns">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-wave-square"></i> Digital Signal Processing</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The analysis and manipulation of signals that have been converted from analog to digital form. This includes sampling, quantization, filtering, and spectral analysis of discrete-time signals.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Discrete-Time Systems</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Z-transforms, difference equations, system response</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Digital Filters</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">FIR, IIR, filter design methods, implementation</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Spectral Analysis</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">DFT, FFT, power spectrum estimation</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-image"></i> Image Processing</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The analysis and manipulation of two-dimensional signals (images). This includes image enhancement, restoration, compression, segmentation, and feature extraction for applications like computer vision and medical imaging.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Image Enhancement</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Contrast adjustment, noise reduction, sharpening</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Image Transforms</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">2D Fourier transform, wavelets, DCT</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Image Analysis</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Segmentation, feature extraction, pattern recognition</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-music"></i> Audio Signal Processing</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The analysis and manipulation of audio signals. This includes speech and music processing, audio compression, noise reduction, and acoustic feature extraction for applications like voice recognition and music information retrieval.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Speech Processing</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Speech recognition, synthesis, enhancement</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Audio Effects</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Reverberation, equalization, time-stretching</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Music Analysis</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Pitch detection, beat tracking, genre classification</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cards-grid three-columns" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-brain"></i> Statistical Signal Processing</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The application of statistical methods to signal processing problems. This includes estimation theory, detection theory, and machine learning approaches for extracting information from noisy or uncertain signals.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Estimation Theory</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Parameter estimation, Kalman filtering, Wiener filtering</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Detection Theory</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Hypothesis testing, ROC analysis, optimal detection</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Adaptive Filtering</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">LMS algorithm, RLS algorithm, adaptive equalization</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-broadcast-tower"></i> Communication Signal Processing</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The processing of signals for communication systems. This includes modulation, demodulation, channel coding, equalization, and synchronization for reliable data transmission over various channels.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Modulation Techniques</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">AM, FM, PSK, QAM, OFDM</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Channel Coding</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Error correction codes, interleaving, LDPC</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Equalization</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Channel estimation, adaptive equalization</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-microchip"></i> Array Signal Processing</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The processing of signals received by an array of sensors. This includes beamforming, direction finding, and spatial filtering for applications like radar, sonar, and wireless communications.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Beamforming</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Conventional, adaptive, and optimal beamforming</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Direction Finding</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">MUSIC, ESPRIT, maximum likelihood methods</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Spatial Filtering</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Interference cancellation, source separation</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

